A board of directors may suspend a director if, considering the directorâ€™s course of conduct and the inadequacy of other available remedies, immediate suspension is necessary for the best interests of the association and the director is engaging, or has engaged, in:
Fraudulent conduct with respect to the association or its members;
Gross abuse of the position of director;
